headline.main: TOKYO IS WATCHED; Washington Is Uneasy Over Orient in Case Moscow Falls ROOSEVELT HOLDS PARLEY Sees Envoy to Italy as Knox Expresses Belief in Russia, Hints Warning to Japan TOKYO IS WATCHED FOR SIGN OF MOVE

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 15 -- Within twenty-four hours after the return to the United States of William Phillips, United States Ambassador to Italy, President Roosevelt held a long conference with the envoy at the White House today.
abstract: Phillips and Roosevelt conf on possibility of taking Italy out of war
